text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia hockingsii is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae that is native to parts of north eastern Australia.
The glabrous and viscid shrub typically grows to a height of up to 3 m (9.8 ft) and has a rounded habit.
The shrub has a limited distribution on the Isla Gorge National Park area of the Central region of Queensland where it is found on sandstone plateaus growing in skeletal sandy soils among Eucalyptus woodland communities.
